  "text": "Since a large part of misspellings found in UGC is phonetically-motivated, [CITATION_1] proposed a phonetic-based speller for correcting such errors. The speller combines edit distance and several specific phonetic rules for Portuguese in order to generate correction candidates. The correction of internet slang and proper name and acronyms capitalization is based on a set of lexicons. Each lexicon contains many pairs of wrong-correct form of words. The correction is performed by looking up the noisy word in the lexicon and substituting it by the correct version. Despite this technique achieving good results in the product review domain, it is not scalable and is too restricted, since there is no form of automatic lexicon-learning. Therefore, it is not suitable for a generic, domain-free normalizer. The results obtained by [CITATION_2] will be further discussed, as they are the main source of comparison for our work.",
